      • addMedicine

        public java.lang.String addMedicine​(java.lang.String name,
                                    double dose,
                                    double costDose,
                                    double frecuency,
                                    int number)
        Description This method allows to add new medicines that were prescription during the hospitalization at the patient stories. pre: The patient clinic story must be not null. post: New medicines were added to the patient clinic story.
        Parameters:
        name - medicine name. This param must be not null.
        dose - medicine dose, this param refers to the amount of medicine supplied to the pet each time according the frequence assigned.
        costDose - medicine cost by each dose. This param could be empty.
        frecuency - frequency of medicine application. This param could be empty.
        number - number of the mini room
        Returns:
        A message that indiques if medicine was added to the patient clinic story
